{
  "texts": [
    "Researchers generally classify fake reviews into the following three types [5] [6] [7].",
    "The first category is untrue opinions, i.e., deliberately posting negative reviews to damage the image of the product/brand or posting positive reviews to promote the product/brand.",
    "The second category is reviews that focus on the product brand rather than the product itself.",
    "The third category is nonreviews, which do not provide real opinions or are just advertisements.",
    "Jindal and Liu 6 are considered pioneers in the automatic detection of fake reviews."
  ]
}